attachments.title: Is OTG supported in USB Type C?
attachments.text: Answer (1 of 3): Yes, full OTG is supported on Type C, as is Power Delivery. Some of the final details are being worked out - the standards are not yet finalised, so there may be software fixes to handle some of the edge cases.

so spending a decent amount of time with the pixel xl at this point.. the screen, :ok_hand:. It’s just so good.

The downside is if you hold the pixel xl in landscape orientation to watch or run full screen content like videos or a game.. you can absolutely hold it wrong blocking the bottom left port hole (which is the speaker port) completely muting the device. It’s worth saying I think the pixel xl is basically as loud as the 6p, not sure if its louder or quieter but definitely loud enough.

Camera :ok_hand:. I have had a few bad photos from it but for the most part no other android device I have used comes close to the photos this takes not even the 6P which was pretty darn good. I have not taken enough video to make a comment on it other than that so far it seems good but nothing significantly better than say the 5x/6p
